properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 3 at 8:31PM CST until January 5 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...STRONG WINDS ACROSS THE LAKE SUNDAY AND SUNDAY NIGHT...

* WHAT...West winds gusting to 30 knots Sunday morning, becoming
west gales to 40 knots by Sunday afternoon and night.

* WHERE...Sheboygan to Winthrop Harbor IL.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, from 6 AM to noon CST
Sunday. For the Gale Watch, from Sunday afternoon through late
Sunday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.
